                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions:</label> The <locus from="iiia" to="iiia">final right
                        flyleaf a side (f. iiia)</locus> bears a description of the volume written
                     in naskh, adjecent to Malet's seal impressions.<lb/>
                     <label>Bookplate and label:</label> the <locus from="Inner_back_cover"
                        to="Inner_back_cover">left paste-down</locus> bears the <q xml:lang="en"
                        >Bibliotheca Lindesiana</q> bookplate with shelf mark <q xml:lang="en"
                        >1/C</q>, and label with class mark <q xml:lang="en">Additional MSS Persian
                           <hi rend="strikethrough">107–108</hi></q> with the numbers crossed out
                     and <q>902</q> written aside. </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding when="1874">
                        <p>Probably uniformly rebound together with <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7413"
                                 ><idno>Persian MS 901</idno></ref> in a modern British style,
                           probably completed for <persName type="standard" role="bsl"
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5679225/" key="person_5679225">Bernard
                              Quaritch (1819–1899)</persName> on behalf of <persName role="fmo"
                              ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058">Alexander
                              Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford (1812–1880)</persName>, with a table of
                           contents appended to the end of this volume. </p>
                        <p>Resewn on five recessed cords laced into
                           <material>pasteboards</material>. Edges trimmed and gilt, with front-bead
                           decorative endbands of white and red threads stitched over flat cores
                           twined at <locus from="Head" to="Head">head</locus> and <locus
                              from="Tail" to="Tail">tail</locus>. Covered in full morocco-grained
                           goatskin <material>leather</material> with a truncated flap (Type II
                           binding per Déroche), with predminantly brown 'shell' patterned marbled
                           endpapers, with blue, red, green, and ochre veins </p>
                        <decoNote type="binding">Board margins blind-tooled with think-and-thin
                           fillets, with the same palleted at head and tail of the <locus
                              from="Spine" to="Spine">spine</locus> and interior dentelles. <locus
                              from="Spine" to="Spine">Spine</locus> titled:<lb/>
                           <q>MIRÁT-I<lb/>AHMADÍ<lb/> II<lb/>PERSIAN MS.<lb/>A. H.
                           1195</q>.</decoNote>
                        <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
                              <height>308</height>
                              <width>192</width>
                              <depth>62</depth>
                           </dimensions></p>
                        <condition>Binding in good condition with abrasion at the board edges and
                           spine faded.</condition>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <seal type="stamp" subtype="rectangle">
                        <p>A small, legible black rectangular seal impression with two stacked
                           thuluth lines with the name of <persName role="pat seal"
                              key="person_f819">Charles Warre Malet</persName>, single-ruled, and
                           dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" from="1781" to="1782">1196 AH
                              (1781–1782 CE)</date> appears onece on folio <locus from="iiia"
                              to="iiia">final right flyleaf a side (f. iiia)</locus>, again on
                              <locus from="355a" to="355a">355a</locus>:<lb/>
                           <q xml:lang="fa">چارس وار مالت ۱۱۹۶</q><lb/>
                           <dimensions type="seal" unit="mm">
                              <height>11</height>
                              <width>15</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
                  <accMat>Table of Contents written on six folios stiched onto a hinge appears at
                     the end of the volume.</accMat>
               </physDesc>



               <history>
                  <origin>Completed for <persName role="seal" key="person_f819">Charles Warre Malet
                        Sir Charles Warre Malet, 1st Baronet (1752–1815)</persName>, probably in
                        <placeName cert="high" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001525"
                        key="place_7001525">Cambay (Kambhat), Gujarat</placeName>
                     <origDate calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when="1781-11-24">7 Ẕī-al-Ḥijjah 1195 AH (24
                        November 1781 CE)</origDate> as per the colophon in <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_7414"><idno>Persian MS
                           902</idno></ref>, folio 702a.</origin>
                  <provenance><p>Thereafter obtained from an unidentified source by <placeName
                           ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7011781">London</placeName>
                        bookseller <persName type="standard" role="bsl"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/5679225/" key="person_5679225">Bernard Quaritch
                           (1819–1899)</persName>, who then advertized it in his <date>Feb.
                           1876</date> catalogue, no. 11584, then sold to <persName type="standard"
                           role="fmo" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/97751058/" key="person_97751058"
                           >Alexander Lindsay, 25th Earl of Crawford (1812–1880)</persName> for 12
                        pounds and sent to the <orgName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/295427552"
                           key="person_295427552">Bibliotheca Lindesiana</orgName> at Haigh Hall,
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010384"
                           key="place_7010384">Wigan</placeName>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <provenance><p>Purchased by <persName role="dnr" key="person_f6379"
                           change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1901">1901</date> from <persName role="fmo"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9985420/" key="person_9985420">James Ludovic
                           Lindsay, 26th Earl of Crawford (1847–1913)</persName>.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Bequeathed by <persName key="person_f6379" change="#prov-markup">Enriqueta
                           Rylands (1843–1908)</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1908"
                           >1908</date> to the <orgName type="corporation" role="rps"
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/312795145/">John Rylands Library</orgName>,
                           <placeName>Manchester</placeName>.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               </history>
